x4freetext: Eight surface barrier detectors.
Self-supporting targets, enriched to 99.4% 24Mg;
nominally 100 microg/cm thick.
Absolute cross sections were obtained by determining
the solid angles of the detectors and the target
thickness by measuring the scattering of 4-5 MeV alpha-
particles from the 24Mg and a thin gold target of known
thickness and analysing the cross sections at forward
angles (<=30 degr.)in terms of the Rutherford
scattering
Corrected for deadtime.
